My bag is at the airport.

13:12.305 --> 13:13.310
- I mean...
- I got you covered.

13:13.377 --> 13:14.993
Why are there
so many bras?

13:15.108 --> 13:17.309
Are women in that big
of a hurry to leave afterwards?

13:17.386 --> 13:20.512
Hey, my love life's kind of
like the airport TGI Fridays.

13:20.589 --> 13:22.747
It is all about
turning those tables.

13:22.824 --> 13:25.494
Look at this. I feel like I'm in
Filene's Basement.

13:26.150 --> 13:28.576
Oh, shit,
I've gotta take this.

13:28.789 --> 13:30.446
Brockmire.
It's Whitney.

13:30.523 --> 13:33.849
Is this a good time?
Well, uh, you tell me.

13:39.833 --> 13:42.392
Hi. I was interested
in changing my flight.

13:42.469 --> 13:44.803
I have a flight tonight,
and I was wondering

13:44.880 --> 13:47.330
what your policy is
about getting reimbursed.

13:47.407 --> 13:49.521
I reviewed the data,
and, overwhelmingly,

13:49.589 --> 13:51.306
it seems like the greatest
benefit to the franchise

13:51.374 --> 13:53.012
would be to go with Raj.

13:53.623 --> 13:55.268
Okay.
That's...

13:55.415 --> 13:59.026
pretty much what I figured.
But I was overruled.

13:59.533 --> 14:00.934
What?

14:03.156 --> 14:04.739
My flight got canceled.

14:05.684 --> 14:07.326
My flight got canceled.

14:09.554 --> 14:10.713
Hey.

14:10.884 --> 14:13.516
You're not gonna believe this,
but my flight got canceled.

14:13.584 --> 14:14.658
Jules, I got it.

14:14.746 --> 14:17.953
I got the job! I am...
I'm going to Atlanta!

14:18.190 --> 14:20.916
- Yeah!
- Wait, what?

14:22.236 --> 14:23.291
How is this possible?

14:23.367 --> 14:25.302
You never mentioned there was
a chance you were leaving.

14:25.369 --> 14:26.779
Jules, I didn't think
there was,

14:26.847 --> 14:28.051
but I gotta get to Atlanta

14:28.119 --> 14:30.036
and press the flesh
of my benefactors.

14:30.104 --> 14:31.786
- When?
- Now.

14:32.007 --> 14:33.248
You're meeting them today?

14:33.316 --> 14:34.995
Well, the meeting's not
till Wednesday,

14:35.063 --> 14:36.345
but I'm taking
the next flight.

14:36.422 --> 14:38.365
- Well, change it.
- Oh, Jules, I would love to.

14:38.436 --> 14:40.383
No, I really would,
but, you know,

14:40.460 --> 14:42.167
I-I-I kind of like
to tool around a city

14:42.235 --> 14:44.948
and get to know it for a couple
of days before I represent it.

14:45.016 --> 14:47.572
I mean, you know...
kinda my process.

14:47.640 --> 14:49.392
Your process?
What are you, Basquiat?

14:49.469 --> 14:50.893
You report things
that people

14:50.961 --> 14:52.361
can already see
with their own eyes.

14:52.429 --> 14:54.297
Well, some people would say
there's kind of an art

14:54.364 --> 14:56.784
- to what I do.
- I changed my flight for you!

14:57.028 --> 14:58.775
You told me it was...
It was cancelled.

14:58.843 --> 15:01.400
I lied! Obviously!

15:01.956 --> 15:04.282
- Jesus, just... Yeah. Call a taxi.
- All right.

15:04.351 --> 15:06.163
No, no, no, no, no.
I'll... I'll push my flight.

15:06.231 --> 15:08.609
- Don't do me any favors.
- Ple... I want to. I do.

15:08.677 --> 15:10.044
Of course,
I wanna push my flight, J...

15:10.111 --> 15:12.661
Hey, come on.
Please don't leave now.

15:17.564 --> 15:18.830
Why not?

15:21.968 --> 15:23.568
Well, beignets.

15:27.016 --> 15:28.419
- What will it be?
- Two beignets,

15:28.487 --> 15:30.212
we know that for sure,
and...

15:30.385 --> 15:31.634
A chicory coffee.

15:31.711 --> 15:34.171
No, uh, regular.
Two regular coffees, please.

15:34.255 --> 15:35.515
Allow me to explain.

15:35.596 --> 15:38.116
Um, chicory
was originally marketed

15:38.184 --> 15:40.844
as kind of a filler
to make coffee go farther.

15:40.921 --> 15:43.245
It's kind of like
it's a dried up old beet root

15:43.322 --> 15:44.855
with absolutely
no caffeine in it.

15:44.932 --> 15:47.525
Drinking chicory coffee
when regular coffee is available

15:47.602 --> 15:51.854
is kind of like seeing a bong full
of fresh Jack Herer and going,

15:51.931 --> 15:53.589
"Nah, no, thanks.
I'll just, uh...

15:53.666 --> 15:55.332
I'll take
that half-smoked spliff

15:55.409 --> 15:57.694
out of that ashtray
over there."

15:57.771 --> 16:00.537
- Do you ever shut up?
- I do not, no.

16:00.614 --> 16:03.053
But, hey, you knew that,
didn't you?

16:04.077 --> 16:06.269
- I'm such an idiot!
- No, you're not.

16:06.346 --> 16:08.145
You're not an idiot.
You didn't know.

16:08.222 --> 16:10.694
Chicory is real popular
around here.

16:14.256 --> 16:15.541
Jules!

16:20.026 --> 16:21.405
What's up?

16:24.933 --> 16:28.349
I started thinking,
"I like it here, and...

16:29.317 --> 16:31.153
I like being with Jim."

16:32.726 --> 16:34.363
If I don't buy
into this team,

16:34.440 --> 16:36.365
that's five months
during the off-season.

16:36.442 --> 16:37.919
Maybe I could split
my time between...

16:37.986 --> 16:40.529
Well, yes. We...
Why can't we do that?

16:40.751 --> 16:42.629
An hour ago,
it was New Orleans.

16:42.697 --> 16:44.425
Now it's Atlanta. What's it
gonna be in six months?

16:44.492 --> 16:47.251
- I can't just follow you around!
- Why not?

16:47.328 --> 16:49.746
Jules, I am...
I am very delightful.

16:49.991 --> 16:52.990
I have a life in Morristown, in
case you forgot. No, I know.

16:53.058 --> 16:54.402
I know better than
to ask you to leave there.

16:54.469 --> 16:56.070
- But, look, Jules...
- Then what are you saying?

16:56.137 --> 16:58.904
I am saying I've been
doing some thinking, too.

16:58.972 --> 17:01.765
Tonight was amazing.
I mean, it was just...

17:01.833 --> 17:03.683
Right? It was unbelievable.

17:03.973 --> 17:05.800
Why can't we meet up
once a month

17:05.903 --> 17:07.195
at one of my road games?

17:07.272 --> 17:09.865
Could be in Miami or St. Louis,
Cincinnati, wherever.

17:09.942 --> 17:11.942
The point is, it will be
a night just like tonight,

17:12.019 --> 17:13.868
we'll be two people,
we won't know anybody.

17:13.938 --> 17:15.553
We'll be free
to just explore a new city.

17:15.621 --> 17:18.290
We can just drink
and dance and just...

17:18.358 --> 17:20.009
screw and...

17:20.086 --> 17:22.644
We can just...
We can disappear, Jules.

17:26.557 --> 17:27.991
So, a bender?

17:28.085 --> 17:31.108
No, okay, yes... no.
But, yes, all right.

17:31.176 --> 17:32.881
Well, just think about it,
just for a second.

17:32.948 --> 17:35.097
All highs, no lows.
Right?

17:35.165 --> 17:37.761
We'll never have to fight over
who empties the dishwasher

17:37.838 --> 17:39.370
or pick up
each other's dry cleaning

17:39.447 --> 17:42.375
or ask each other,
"How was your day, hon?"

17:42.443 --> 17:43.451
Jules, I'll never
have to pretend

17:43.518 --> 17:44.968
that I didn't
just hear you fart.

17:45.143 --> 17:47.111
Okay, think about that.
No, wait... no, really!

17:47.188 --> 17:49.247
We just cut out all
the mundane bullshit

17:49.324 --> 17:52.492
and get right to
the perfect relationship.

17:55.685 --> 17:58.444
The "mundane bullshit"
<i>is</i> a relationship.

17:58.624 --> 18:00.801
Yeah, but I know, but why settle
for that when we can...

18:00.868 --> 18:04.871
You know, we can make up our own rules!
Because I'd still be settling.

18:05.295 --> 18:07.068
I want someone to have
a night like tonight with

18:07.136 --> 18:08.951
who'll also be there
when I wake up in the morning.

18:09.018 --> 18:10.093
I want to have adventures
with someone,

18:10.160 --> 18:13.221
but I also want someone
to pay the bills with and...

18:13.349 --> 18:14.545
go grocery shopping

18:14.613 --> 18:17.213
and tell me when it's time
to wash my smelly jeans.

18:17.281 --> 18:19.728
And I deserve all that.
Jules, you do.

18:19.809 --> 18:21.611
Dear God, you do.

18:22.749 --> 18:25.441
It's all I can offer you
right now, though.

18:26.753 --> 18:30.200
You have a choice, and you're not
choosing me... again!

18:30.365 --> 18:33.029
Come on. That's a very harsh way
to put it.

18:33.354 --> 18:35.688
What are you doing? I was gonna
take you to the airport.

18:35.920 --> 18:39.097
I won't subject you
to that mundane shit,<i> hon.</i>

18:42.217 --> 18:43.936
Your beignets
are ready.

19:28.247 --> 19:29.278
Hey.

19:29.415 --> 19:31.876
- I'll have what he's having.
- What?

19:32.432 --> 19:34.277
It's a callback,
asshole.

19:34.758 --> 19:36.657
Give me
a Sazerac, neat.

19:41.627 --> 19:44.821
Well, everybody, I want you
to enjoy yourselves!

19:44.898 --> 19:47.098
Soak up every last moment
of New Orleans

19:47.175 --> 19:49.025
that you possibly can.
Why?

19:49.235 --> 19:51.911
Because the sea levels,
they are rising faster

19:51.979 --> 19:54.988
than even the most dire
predictions, and nobody,

19:55.056 --> 19:58.848
and I mean <i> nobody</i> in power
seems to give a shit about that.

19:58.973 --> 20:01.090
Two generations. Two.

20:01.174 --> 20:03.964
All the above-ground cemeteries,
they're gonna be underwater.

20:04.075 --> 20:07.251
So, uh... yeah, we're all
just playing a fiddle

20:07.328 --> 20:09.249
while Rome drowns,
aren't we?

20:09.379 --> 20:11.385
So <i> salud.</i>

20:16.573 --> 20:17.905
What's so funny
down there?

20:18.070 --> 20:20.321
Oh, nothing, Al Gore.

20:20.562 --> 20:23.726
Thanks for
the climate-change lecture.

20:23.803 --> 20:25.694
I'll be sure
to buy a Prius.

20:25.972 --> 20:27.564
Not saying we should
try to stop it.

20:27.632 --> 20:31.159
I'm saying we should embrace it.
Just embrace the futility.

20:32.690 --> 20:36.420
You sound like a junior-high kid
who just discovered Nietzsche.

20:36.547 --> 20:39.947
Yeah, well, it's not my first
nihilist rodeo, I assure you.

20:44.832 --> 20:50.354
So you really think
our actions are meaningless?

20:50.538 --> 20:51.959
That...

20:52.834 --> 20:55.201
consequences
don't matter?

20:57.243 --> 20:58.641
Prove it.

20:59.669 --> 21:01.810
And how would you
like me to do that?

21:05.331 --> 21:08.501
Oh, shit!

21:12.584 --> 21:15.914
- What the hell are you doing?!
- Looking for my Tide Pen.

21:16.227 --> 21:18.321
Jesus Christ!

21:18.528 --> 21:21.109
When you're really ready to go
down the rabbit hole,

21:21.202 --> 21:22.404
call me.

21:23.329 --> 21:24.867
All right, okay.

21:25.159 --> 21:26.617
Shit.

21:31.487 --> 21:33.556
Are you...
Are you all right?

21:33.703 --> 21:35.336
Mm-hmm.

